frameDefinitions: An Agent acts so as to be the strongest force, or most important causal factor in some Situation, to the exclusion of other competing actors.
An Offerer indicates that he or she is able and willing to give a Theme to a Potential_recipient.
This frame is for words that denote highly schematic entities.
A Possible_event is deemed to have all pre-conditions satisfied; in other words, it has some probability of occurrence, if some (generally implicit) further Condition pertains.
This frame concerns permanent organizations (the Institutions) that are intended to help members of the Target_group in a particular Domain with a Service_action.
A Helper benefits a Benefited_party by enabling the culmination of a Goal that the Benefited_party has.
frameExamples: York <t>dominated</t> the game as they held the ball on offense almost the entire 70 minutes.
The host graciously <t>offered</t> us food and drink.
We found an unusual wooden <t>object</t> in the desert.
The Red Cross Tracing and Message Service is a <t>service</t> for finding and reuniting families separated by war and disaster.
Will you <t>help</t> the Government find your brother?
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Agent</fen> is the most forceful and pivotal factor in the situation.
The <fen>Situation</fen> is primarily affected by the <fen>Agent</fen>, in particular how it develops or concludes.
The <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> is dominant.
The location where the domination takes place.
The person that begins in possession of the <fen>Theme</fen> and offers it to the <fen>Potential_recipient</fen> .
The entity that ends up in possession of the <fen>Theme</fen>.
The object which is offered for transfer.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the <fen>Offerer</fen> offers the <fen>Theme</fen> to the <fen>Potential_recipient</fen>.
The <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Offerer</fen> offers the <fen>Theme</fen> to the <fen>Potential_recipient</fen>.
A thing (either abstract or physical) that exists with some degree of permanence.
The <fen>Possible_event</fen> has met its preconditions, and will occur if some further <fen>Condition</fen> holds.
The state-of-affairs that does not hold, but if it did, the <fen>Possible_event</fen> would occur.
The time at which the <fen>Possible_event</fen> can occur.
A permanent organization with a socially important purpose.
The concern of the <fen>Institution</fen>-- broadly speaking, the aspect of society that they affect.
The members of the public whom the <fen>Institution</fen> is intended to serve.
The action performed or enabled by the <fen>Institution</fen> for the <fen>Target_group</fen>.
The <fen>Benefited_party</fen> receives a benefit from the action of the <fen>Helper</fen>.
The <fen>Helper</fen> performs some action that benefits the <fen>Benefited_party</fen>.
The desirable state of affairs that the <fen>Benefited_party</fen> is involved in and which is enabled by the <fen>Helper</fen>.
This role identifies a <fen>Focal_entity</fen> involved in achieving the <fen>Goal</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the Assistance occurs.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the Assistance occurs.

Reach Out ! is a service <fex>for helping young Australians through tough times</fex>.
Whoever didn't cook has to help <fex>with the dishes</fex>.
